FBIS4-17397 "drsov079_d_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 Regional Affairs Troops Move Into N. Ossetia-Ingushetia Corridor Troops Move Into N. Ossetia-Ingushetia Corridor LD2304162094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1600 GMT 23 Apr 94 LD2304162094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] In accordance with a decision of the interim administration in the state of emergency area in North Ossetia and Ingushetia, Russian Internal Affairs Ministry internal troops conducted an operation on Saturday to move into the 8-kilometer security corridor. The interior troops task is to occupy the entire corridor. All North Ossetian and Ingush law enforcement units were pulled out of the corridor in advance. The RIA agency reports that the operation aimed at occupying the security corridor has proceeded without any major complications. Only near the village of Ali-Yurt in Ingushetia did a group of local resident try to prevent the interior troops from carrying out their operational task. The incident was settled promptly and without bloodshed.
